cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource allocation and trajectory design for UAV-enabled communication systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with the trajectory design of UAVs, which is a key aspect of robotics. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimizing the subcarrier allocation policy to maximize the communication system throughput, which is related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design of a system (UAV-enabled communication system) and its control (trajectory design), which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed algorithm for obtaining a locally optimal solution can be considered as an AI-based approach, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
